container.heading: Maryland Medicaid Managed Care Program: Non-Capitated Covered Services

section.heading: Scope.
section.text: This chapter describes the services that are not the responsibility of the MCOs but are covered by the Department on a fee-for-service basis.

para.text: An MCO is not responsible for reimbursing for the following substance use disorder services, regardless of diagnosis:
Services delivered by a community-based provider as described in COMAR 10.09.80 with the following procedure codes:

para.text: Substance use disorder services provided to children in an ICF-A with the revenue code 0100, Residential Services, child and adolescent.
An MCO is not responsible for reimbursing for the following services performed by free-standing laboratories, regardless of diagnosis:
Presumptive drug tests; and
Definitive drug tests.
An MCO is not responsible for reimbursing for the laboratory services described in §B of this regulation unless billed by a:
Primary care provider; or
Other somatic care provider.
An MCO is not responsible for reimbursing for the following substance use disorder services if the MCO is billed with a primary diagnosis listed in §M of this regulation:
Services delivered by an inpatient hospital with the following revenue codes:

tr.td: Room and Board, Private Bed, Psychiatric
Room and Board, Private Bed, Detoxification
Room and Board, Semi-Private Bed, Psychiatric
Room and Board, Semi-Private Bed, Detoxification

para.text: Services delivered by an outpatient hospital with the following revenue codes:
Services delivered by an emergency department with the following revenue codes:

An MCO is not responsible for reimbursing for mental health services with a primary diagnosis listed in §N of this regulation when the services are provided by a hospital and the services are the result of the treatment of mental health diagnosis.
An MCO shall be responsible for reimbursing for behavioral health services delivered by the participant’s primary care provider.
An MCO shall be responsible for reimbursing for somatic services related to gender identity disorder, including gender reassignment surgery.
An MCO is not responsible for reimbursing the behavioral poisoning diagnoses listed in §P of this regulation in an emergency department setting.

An MCO is not responsible for services billed by specialty mental health providers listed in COMAR 10.09.59 when the bill includes the specialty behavioral health diagnoses listed in §M or N in the primary diagnosis field.
An MCO is not responsible for reimbursement of behavioral health crisis services as described in COMAR 10.09.16.
An MCO is not responsible for behavioral health medications.
An MCO is not responsible for reimbursing for services billed by a physician related to prescribing buprenorphine or Vivitrol when the following conditions are met:
The physician delivering buprenorphine has a DATA 2000 waiver;
The physician is not the participant’s primary care provider;
The primary diagnosis is substance use disorder;
The primary reason for the visit is substance use disorder treatment; and
The procedure code listed on the claims is one of the following:

section.heading: Nonbehavioral Health Fee-For-Service Benefits.
section.text: An MCO may not be required to provide any of the following benefits or services that are reimbursed directly by the Department:

para.text: The remaining days of a hospital admission following enrollment in the MCO if the recipient was admitted to the hospital before the date of the recipient's enrollment;
Long-term care services except for those outlined in COMAR 10.67.06.07B and COMAR 10.67.06.12A;
Intermediate Care Facilities for Individuals with Intellectual Disabilities or Persons with Related Conditions (ICF/IID) services;
Personal care services pursuant to COMAR 10.09.20;
Medical day care services, for adults and children;
The following HIV/AIDS services:
Genotypic, phenotypic, or other HIV/AIDS drug resistance testing used in the treatment of HIV/AIDS, if the service is:
Rendered by a Department-approved provider; and
Medically necessary; and
Viral load testing used in treatment of HIV/AIDS.
Physical therapy, speech therapy, and occupational therapy services when:
The enrollee is younger than 21 years old; and
The services are not part of home health services or an inpatient hospital stay;
Augmentative communication devices;
All dental services including but not limited to outpatient surgery fees for the facility and general anesthesia.
Except when a woman has been determined eligible for Medical Assistance benefits under COMAR 10.09.11, an abortion pursuant to COMAR 10.09.02.04G;
Emergency transportation;
Transportation services provided through grants to local governments pursuant to COMAR 10.09.19;
Services provided to members participating in the State's Health Home Program as described in COMAR 10.09.33;
Applied behavioral analysis (ABA) services as described in COMAR 10.09.28; and
Abortions performed in accordance with Health-General Article, § 15-103, Annotated Code of Maryland.
